personalInfo.splInterest: Skiing, scuba diving, painting, string instruments, piano

tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt - Finished 11-45 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament (subject to second reshuffle)
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Finished 13th at the 2015 Big Ten Championships for his best career finish...Went 3-0 in the Big Ten Match Play Championships...Finished the 2014 Florida Open as the low amateur...Won the West Florida Golf Tour Ritz-Carlton Series, a one-day professional event, in September 2013.
tourBios.personal: Would like to open a sport agency if he had not become a professional golfer...Earliest golf memory is making a hole-in-one in a junior tournament...Has a snow leopard as one of his head covers...Best sporting event he attended was the 2008 Summer Olympics' opening ceremony in Beijing...Not many people know he likes to bungee jump...After earning his Web.com Tour card at the Qualifying Tournament, he celebrated by going sky-diving...He is an accomplished violinist who served as his school's orchestral concertmaster in 2012-13 and performed as a volunteer violinist with the Venice Symphony from 2011-13...Skipped a grade in high school and enrolled at Northwestern University as a 17-year-old.
